{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":301,"text":"I'd like to talk today\nabout the two biggest social trends"},{"time":5523,"text":"in the coming century,"},{"time":7000,"text":"and perhaps in the next 10,000 years."},{"time":10159,"text":"But I want to start\nwith my work on romantic love,"},{"time":14000,"text":"because that's my most recent work."},{"time":16222,"text":"What I and my colleagues did was put\n32 people, who were madly in love,"},{"time":21000,"text":"into a functional MRI brain scanner."},{"time":23368,"text":"17 who were madly in love\nand their love was accepted;"},{"time":26241,"text":"and 15 who were madly in love\nand they had just been dumped."},{"time":30032,"text":"And so I want to tell you\nabout that first,"},{"time":32374,"text":"and then go on into where\nI think love is going."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36689,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":38483,"text":"\"What 'tis to love?\" Shakespeare said."},{"time":42538,"text":"I think our ancestors --"},{"time":44480,"text":"I think human beings have been\nwondering about this question"},{"time":48402,"text":"since they sat around their campfires"},{"time":50202,"text":"or lay and watched\nthe stars a million years ago."},{"time":54928,"text":"I started out by trying to figure out\nwhat romantic love was"},{"time":58183,"text":"by looking at the last 45 years\nof the psychological research"},{"time":63690,"text":"and as it turns out,"},{"time":65021,"text":"there's a very specific group of things\nthat happen when you fall in love."},{"time":69568,"text":"The first thing that happens is,"},{"time":72000,"text":"a person begins to take on\nwhat I call, \"special meaning.\""},{"time":75553,"text":"As a truck driver once said to me,"},{"time":77219,"text":"\"The world had a new center,\nand that center was Mary Anne.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":81801,"text":"George Bernard Shaw said it differently."},{"time":83785,"text":"\"Love consists of overestimating\nthe differences"},{"time":86277,"text":"between one woman and another.\""},{"time":88309,"text":"And indeed, that's what we do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":90595,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":93873,"text":"And then you just focus on this person."},{"time":96493,"text":"You can list what you\ndon't like about them,"},{"time":99334,"text":"but then you sweep that aside\nand focus on what you do."},{"time":102922,"text":"As Chaucer said, \"Love is blind.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":106530,"text":"In trying to understand romantic love,"},{"time":108715,"text":"I decided I would read poetry\nfrom all over the world,"},{"time":111716,"text":"and I just want to give\nyou one very short poem"},{"time":114392,"text":"from eighth-century China,"},{"time":115663,"text":"because it's an almost perfect example"},{"time":117896,"text":"of a man who is focused totally\non a particular woman."},{"time":121824,"text":"It's a little bit like when you are\nmadly in love with somebody"},{"time":124888,"text":"and you walk into a parking lot --"},{"time":126550,"text":"their car is different\nfrom every other car in the parking lot."},{"time":129954,"text":"Their wine glass at dinner"},{"time":131484,"text":"is different from every other wine glass\nat the dinner party."},{"time":135000,"text":"And in this case, a man got hooked\non a bamboo sleeping mat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":139312,"text":"And it goes like this."},{"time":140535,"text":"It's by a guy called Yuan Zhen."},{"time":143423,"text":"\"I cannot bear to put away\nthe bamboo sleeping mat."},{"time":146637,"text":"The night I brought you home,\nI watched you roll it out.\""},{"time":150468,"text":"He became hooked on a sleeping mat,"},{"time":152849,"text":"probably because of elevated activity\nof dopamine in his brain,"},{"time":155849,"text":"just like with you and me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":157294,"text":"But anyway, not only does this person\ntake on special meaning,"},{"time":160483,"text":"you focus your attention on them."},{"time":162953,"text":"You aggrandize them."},{"time":164578,"text":"But you have intense energy."},{"time":166363,"text":"As one Polynesian said,\n\"I felt like jumping in the sky.\""},{"time":170406,"text":"You're up all night.\nYou're walking till dawn."},{"time":173627,"text":"You feel intense elation\nwhen things are going well;"},{"time":176610,"text":"mood swings into horrible despair\nwhen things are going poorly."},{"time":180183,"text":"Real dependence on this person."},{"time":182661,"text":"As one businessman in New York said to me,"},{"time":185084,"text":"\"Anything she liked, I liked.\""},{"time":187524,"text":"Simple. Romantic love is very simple."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190793,"text":"You become extremely sexually possessive."},{"time":193000,"text":"You know, if you're just sleeping\nwith somebody casually,"},{"time":195755,"text":"you don't really care\nif they're sleeping with somebody else."},{"time":198649,"text":"But the moment you fall in love,"},{"time":200227,"text":"you become extremely\nsexually possessive of them."},{"time":202547,"text":"I think there's a Darwinian\npurpose to this."},{"time":206000,"text":"The whole point of this\nis to pull two people together"},{"time":208657,"text":"strongly enough to begin\nto rear babies as a team."}]},{"cues":[{"time":213000,"text":"But the main characteristics\nof romantic love are craving:"},{"time":216000,"text":"an intense craving\nto be with a particular person,"},{"time":219446,"text":"not just sexually, but emotionally."},{"time":221693,"text":"It would be nice to go to bed with them,"},{"time":225445,"text":"but you want them to call you\non the telephone, to invite you out, etc.,"},{"time":229701,"text":"to tell you that they love you."},{"time":232460,"text":"The other main characteristic\nis motivation."},{"time":237206,"text":"The motor in the brain begins to crank,\nand you want this person."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241000,"text":"And last but not least,\nit is an obsession."},{"time":244174,"text":"Before I put these people\nin the MRI machine,"},{"time":248000,"text":"I would ask them all kinds of questions."},{"time":250000,"text":"But my most important question\nwas always the same."},{"time":253189,"text":"It was: \"What percentage of the day\nand night do you think about this person?\""},{"time":258000,"text":"And indeed, they would say,"},{"time":259914,"text":"\"All day. All night."},{"time":262095,"text":"I can never stop thinking\nabout him or her.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":265000,"text":"And then, the very last question --"},{"time":266834,"text":"I would always have to work\nmyself up to this question,"},{"time":269457,"text":"because I'm not a psychologist."},{"time":271048,"text":"I don't work with people\nin any kind of traumatic situation."},{"time":274394,"text":"My final question was always the same."},{"time":276323,"text":"I would say,\n\"Would you die for him or her?\""},{"time":279465,"text":"And, indeed, these people would say \"Yes!\""},{"time":281560,"text":"as if I had asked them to pass the salt."},{"time":283695,"text":"I was just staggered by it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":287634,"text":"So we scanned their brains,"},{"time":290244,"text":"looking at a photograph\nof their sweetheart"},{"time":292378,"text":"and looking at a neutral photograph,"},{"time":294170,"text":"with a distraction task in between."},{"time":296028,"text":"So we could look at the same brain\nwhen it was in that heightened state"},{"time":301000,"text":"and when it was in a resting state."},{"time":303869,"text":"And we found activity\nin a lot of brain regions."},{"time":306164,"text":"In fact, one of the most important\nwas a brain region"},{"time":308846,"text":"that becomes active\nwhen you feel the rush of cocaine."},{"time":312657,"text":"And indeed, that's exactly what happens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":315650,"text":"I began to realize that romantic love\nis not an emotion."},{"time":320293,"text":"In fact, I had always thought\nit was a series of emotions,"},{"time":323173,"text":"from very high to very low."},{"time":324903,"text":"But actually, it's a drive."},{"time":326633,"text":"It comes from the motor of the mind,"},{"time":328792,"text":"the wanting part of the mind,\nthe craving part of the mind."},{"time":332481,"text":"The kind of part of the mind"},{"time":334000,"text":"when you're reaching\nfor that piece of chocolate,"},{"time":336664,"text":"when you want to win\nthat promotion at work."},{"time":340906,"text":"The motor of the brain."},{"time":342469,"text":"It's a drive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":343697,"text":"And in fact, I think it's more powerful\nthan the sex drive."},{"time":347166,"text":"You know, if you ask somebody\nto go to bed with you,"},{"time":349673,"text":"and they say, \"No, thank you,\""},{"time":351134,"text":"you certainly don't kill yourself\nor slip into a clinical depression."},{"time":354675,"text":"But certainly, around the world,"},{"time":357892,"text":"people who are rejected\nin love will kill for it."},{"time":362349,"text":"People live for love."},{"time":363508,"text":"They kill for love."},{"time":364792,"text":"They die for love."},{"time":366277,"text":"They have songs, poems, novels,"},{"time":369879,"text":"sculptures, paintings, myths, legends."},{"time":373847,"text":"In over 175 societies,"},{"time":376020,"text":"people have left their evidence\nof this powerful brain system."},{"time":380828,"text":"I have come to think"},{"time":381875,"text":"it's one of the most powerful\nbrain systems on Earth"},{"time":384487,"text":"for both great joy and great sorrow."}]},{"cues":[{"time":387659,"text":"And I've also come to think"},{"time":389121,"text":"that it's one of three\nbasically different brain systems"},{"time":392628,"text":"that evolved from mating and reproduction."},{"time":395072,"text":"One is the sex drive:\nthe craving for sexual gratification."},{"time":398555,"text":"W.H. Auden called it\nan \"intolerable neural itch,\""},{"time":402000,"text":"and indeed, that's what it is."},{"time":405142,"text":"It keeps bothering you\na little bit, like being hungry."},{"time":408904,"text":"The second of these three brain\nsystems is romantic love:"},{"time":411874,"text":"that elation, obsession of early love."},{"time":414000,"text":"And the third brain system is attachment:"},{"time":416380,"text":"that sense of calm and security\nyou can feel for a long-term partner."}]},{"cues":[{"time":420698,"text":"And I think that the sex drive\nevolved to get you out there,"},{"time":423534,"text":"looking for a whole range of partners."},{"time":426113,"text":"You can feel it when you're just\ndriving along in your car."},{"time":428922,"text":"It can be focused on nobody."},{"time":430318,"text":"I think romantic love evolved\nto enable you to focus your mating energy"},{"time":434000,"text":"on just one individual at a time,"},{"time":436000,"text":"thereby conserving mating time and energy."},{"time":438856,"text":"And I think that attachment,\nthe third brain system,"},{"time":441610,"text":"evolved to enable you to tolerate\nthis human being"},{"time":445176,"text":"at least long enough to raise\na child together as a team."},{"time":451000,"text":"So with that preamble,"},{"time":452522,"text":"I want to go into discussing\nthe two most profound social trends."},{"time":459000,"text":"One of the last 10,000 years"},{"time":461307,"text":"and the other,\ncertainly of the last 25 years,"},{"time":466028,"text":"that are going to have an impact\non these three different brain systems:"},{"time":470304,"text":"lust, romantic love\nand deep attachment to a partner."}]},{"cues":[{"time":474262,"text":"The first is women working,\nmoving into the workforce."},{"time":481333,"text":"I've looked at 130 societies"},{"time":484248,"text":"through the demographic yearbooks\nof the United Nations."},{"time":486913,"text":"Everywhere in the world,\n129 out of 130 of them,"},{"time":491669,"text":"women are not only moving\ninto the job market --"},{"time":494000,"text":"sometimes very, very slowly,\nbut they are moving into the job market --"},{"time":498000,"text":"and they are very slowly closing\nthat gap between men and women"},{"time":501878,"text":"in terms of economic power,\nhealth and education."},{"time":505699,"text":"It's very slow."}]},{"cues":[{"time":506859,"text":"For every trend on this planet,\nthere's a counter-trend."},{"time":510000,"text":"We all know of them, but nevertheless --"},{"time":512337,"text":"the Arabs say, \"The dogs may bark,\nbut the caravan moves on.\""},{"time":518757,"text":"And, indeed, that caravan is moving on."},{"time":521108,"text":"Women are moving back into the job market."},{"time":523819,"text":"And I say back into the job market,\nbecause this is not new."},{"time":527323,"text":"For millions of years,\non the grasslands of Africa,"},{"time":531013,"text":"women commuted to work\nto gather their vegetables."},{"time":534187,"text":"They came home with 60 to 80 percent\nof the evening meal."},{"time":537871,"text":"The double income family was the standard."},{"time":540783,"text":"And women were regarded\nas just as economically,"},{"time":544237,"text":"socially and sexually powerful as men."},{"time":548000,"text":"In short, we're really\nmoving forward to the past."}]},{"cues":[{"time":552223,"text":"Then, women's worst\ninvention was the plow."},{"time":557540,"text":"With the beginning of plow agriculture,\nmen's roles became extremely powerful."},{"time":561238,"text":"Women lost their ancient\njobs as collectors,"},{"time":565698,"text":"but then with the industrial revolution\nand the post-industrial revolution"},{"time":569401,"text":"they're moving back into the job market."},{"time":571368,"text":"In short, they are acquiring the status\nthat they had a million years ago,"},{"time":576519,"text":"10,000 years ago, 100,000 years ago."},{"time":579767,"text":"We are seeing now one\nof the most remarkable traditions"},{"time":584362,"text":"in the history of the human animal."},{"time":588666,"text":"And it's going to have an impact."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590286,"text":"I generally give a whole lecture"},{"time":591843,"text":"on the impact of women\non the business community."},{"time":594171,"text":"I'll say just a couple of things,\nand then go on to sex and love."},{"time":597252,"text":"There's a lot of gender differences;"},{"time":599133,"text":"anybody who thinks men and women are alike"},{"time":601333,"text":"simply never had a boy and a girl child."},{"time":603299,"text":"I don't know why they want to think\nthat men and women are alike."},{"time":606516,"text":"There's much we have in common,"},{"time":608063,"text":"but there's a whole lot\nthat we do not have in common."}]},{"cues":[{"time":611000,"text":"We are -- in the words of Ted Hughes,"},{"time":613000,"text":"\"I think that we are like two feet.\nWe need each other to get ahead.\""},{"time":618128,"text":"But we did not evolve\nto have the same brain."},{"time":621000,"text":"And we're finding more and more\ngender differences in the brain."},{"time":624473,"text":"I'll only just use a couple\nand then move on to sex and love."},{"time":627624,"text":"One of them is women's verbal ability."},{"time":629755,"text":"Women can talk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":631000,"text":"Women's ability to find the right word\nrapidly, basic articulation"},{"time":635000,"text":"goes up in the middle\nof the menstrual cycle,"},{"time":637402,"text":"when estrogen levels peak."},{"time":638997,"text":"But even at menstruation,\nthey're better than the average man."},{"time":643099,"text":"Women can talk."},{"time":644655,"text":"They've been doing it for a million years;\nwords were women's tools."},{"time":648000,"text":"They held that baby\nin front of their face,"},{"time":650111,"text":"cajoling it, reprimanding it,\neducating it with words."},{"time":653944,"text":"And, indeed, they're becoming\na very powerful force."}]},{"cues":[{"time":657000,"text":"Even in places like India and Japan,"},{"time":662261,"text":"where women are not moving rapidly\ninto the regular job market,"},{"time":665682,"text":"they're moving into journalism."},{"time":667539,"text":"And I think that the television\nis like the global campfire."},{"time":672000,"text":"We sit around it and it shapes our minds."},{"time":676000,"text":"Almost always, when I'm on TV,\nthe producer who calls me,"},{"time":680108,"text":"who negotiates what we're going to say,"},{"time":682275,"text":"is a woman."},{"time":683354,"text":"In fact, Solzhenitsyn once said,"},{"time":686036,"text":"\"To have a great writer\nis to have another government.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":689682,"text":"Today 54 percent of people\nwho are writers in America are women."},{"time":695158,"text":"It's one of many, many\ncharacteristics that women have"},{"time":697855,"text":"that they will bring into the job market."},{"time":700159,"text":"They've got incredible people skills,\nnegotiating skills."},{"time":704310,"text":"They're highly imaginative."},{"time":706000,"text":"We now know the brain circuitry\nof imagination, of long-term planning."},{"time":710603,"text":"They tend to be web thinkers."},{"time":712747,"text":"Because the female parts\nof the brain are better connected,"},{"time":715556,"text":"they tend to collect more\npieces of data when they think,"},{"time":718754,"text":"put them into more complex patterns,\nsee more options and outcomes."},{"time":723481,"text":"They tend to be contextual,\nholistic thinkers,"},{"time":727211,"text":"what I call web thinkers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":728775,"text":"Men tend to -- and these are averages --"},{"time":730804,"text":"tend to get rid of what they regard\nas extraneous,"},{"time":733487,"text":"focus on what they do,"},{"time":734896,"text":"and move in a more\nstep-by-step thinking pattern."},{"time":741171,"text":"They're both perfectly good\nways of thinking."},{"time":743297,"text":"We need both of them to get ahead."},{"time":745553,"text":"In fact, there's many more\nmale geniuses in the world."},{"time":749000,"text":"And there's also many more\nmale idiots in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":751745,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":753495,"text":"When the male brain works well,\nit works extremely well."},{"time":756701,"text":"And what I really think\nthat we're doing is,"},{"time":760059,"text":"we're moving towards\na collaborative society,"},{"time":762369,"text":"a society in which the talents\nof both men and women"},{"time":765195,"text":"are becoming understood\nand valued and employed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":769000,"text":"But in fact, women moving\ninto the job market"},{"time":771787,"text":"is having a huge impact\non sex and romance and family life."},{"time":777608,"text":"Foremost, women are starting\nto express their sexuality."},{"time":782716,"text":"I'm always astonished\nwhen people come to me and say,"},{"time":785366,"text":"\"Why is it that men are so adulterous?\""},{"time":787708,"text":"\"Why do you think\nmore men are adulterous than women?\""},{"time":790445,"text":"\"Well, men are more adulterous!\""},{"time":792040,"text":"And I say, \"Who do you think\nthese men are sleeping with?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":795002,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":796430,"text":"And -- basic math!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":798182,"text":"Anyway."},{"time":799380,"text":"In the Western world,"},{"time":803000,"text":"women start sooner at sex,\nhave more partners,"},{"time":806000,"text":"express less remorse\nfor the partners that they do,"},{"time":808909,"text":"marry later, have fewer children,"},{"time":811615,"text":"leave bad marriages\nin order to get good ones."},{"time":814544,"text":"We are seeing the rise\nof female sexual expression."},{"time":818547,"text":"And, indeed, once again we're moving\nforward to the kind of sexual expression"},{"time":823292,"text":"that we probably saw on the grasslands\nof Africa a million years ago,"},{"time":827000,"text":"because this is the kind\nof sexual expression that we see"},{"time":830000,"text":"in hunting and gathering societies today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":832865,"text":"We're also returning\nto an ancient form of marriage equality."},{"time":837420,"text":"They're now saying that the 21st century"},{"time":842000,"text":"is going to be the century of what\nthey call the \"symmetrical marriage,\""},{"time":846000,"text":"or the \"pure marriage,\"\nor the \"companionate marriage.\""},{"time":851408,"text":"This is a marriage between equals,"},{"time":855000,"text":"moving forward to a pattern"},{"time":857467,"text":"that is highly compatible\nwith the ancient human spirit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":861775,"text":"We're also seeing a rise of romantic love."},{"time":864786,"text":"91 percent of American women\nand 86 percent of American men"},{"time":869036,"text":"would not marry somebody\nwho had every single quality"},{"time":873663,"text":"they were looking for in a partner,"},{"time":875503,"text":"if they were not in love with that person."},{"time":878290,"text":"People around the world,\nin a study of 37 societies,"},{"time":881833,"text":"want to be in love\nwith the person that they marry."},{"time":885946,"text":"Indeed, arranged marriages are\non their way off this braid of human life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":895618,"text":"I even think that marriages\nmight even become more stable"},{"time":898436,"text":"because of the second great world trend."},{"time":902214,"text":"The first one being women\nmoving into the job market,"},{"time":905000,"text":"the second one being\nthe aging world population."},{"time":907874,"text":"They're now saying that in America,"},{"time":910325,"text":"that middle age should be regarded\nas up to age 85."},{"time":914642,"text":"Because in that highest\nage category of 76 to 85,"},{"time":919545,"text":"as much as 40 percent of people\nhave nothing really wrong with them."},{"time":923000,"text":"So we're seeing there's a real\nextension of middle age."}]},{"cues":[{"time":926714,"text":"For one of my books,\nI looked at divorce data in 58 societies."},{"time":932000,"text":"And as it turns out, the older you get,\nthe less likely you are to divorce."},{"time":936596,"text":"So the divorce rate right now\nis stable in America,"},{"time":940221,"text":"and it's actually beginning to decline."},{"time":942579,"text":"It may decline some more."},{"time":947133,"text":"I would even say that with Viagra,"},{"time":951156,"text":"estrogen replacement, hip replacements"},{"time":954995,"text":"and the incredibly interesting women"},{"time":957000,"text":"-- women have never been\nas interesting as they are now."},{"time":960129,"text":"Not at any time on this planet\nhave women been so educated,"},{"time":963611,"text":"so interesting, so capable."},{"time":965962,"text":"And so I honestly think that if there\nreally was ever a time in human evolution"},{"time":971365,"text":"when we have the opportunity to make\ngood marriages, that time is now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":976516,"text":"However, there's always kinds\nof complications in this."},{"time":979741,"text":"These three brain systems --\nlust, romantic love and attachment --"},{"time":984482,"text":"don't always go together."},{"time":985860,"text":"They can go together, by the way."},{"time":987583,"text":"That's why casual sex isn't so casual."},{"time":989559,"text":"With orgasm you get a spike of dopamine."},{"time":991852,"text":"Dopamine's associated with romantic love,"},{"time":993972,"text":"and you can just\nfall in love with somebody"},{"time":996019,"text":"who you're just having casual sex with."},{"time":997906,"text":"With orgasm, then you get a real rush\nof oxytocin and vasopressin --"},{"time":1001366,"text":"those are associated with attachment."},{"time":1003421,"text":"This is why you can feel such a sense\nof cosmic union with somebody"},{"time":1007404,"text":"after you've made love to them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1009277,"text":"But these three brain systems:\nlust, romantic love and attachment,"},{"time":1014000,"text":"aren't always connected to each other."},{"time":1017000,"text":"You can feel deep attachment\nto a long-term partner"},{"time":1020275,"text":"while you feel intense\nromantic love for somebody else,"},{"time":1024391,"text":"while you feel the sex drive for people\nunrelated to these other partners."},{"time":1030312,"text":"In short, we're capable of loving\nmore than one person at a time."},{"time":1035714,"text":"In fact, you can lie in bed at night"},{"time":1037730,"text":"and swing from deep feelings\nof attachment for one person"},{"time":1041000,"text":"to deep feelings\nof romantic love for somebody else."},{"time":1044456,"text":"It's as if there's a committee meeting\ngoing on in your head"},{"time":1047361,"text":"as you are trying to decide what to do."},{"time":1050512,"text":"So I don't think, honestly,"},{"time":1052171,"text":"we're an animal\nthat was built to be happy;"},{"time":1054210,"text":"we are an animal\nthat was built to reproduce."},{"time":1056502,"text":"I think the happiness we find, we make."},{"time":1059461,"text":"And I think, however,"},{"time":1062967,"text":"we can make good relationships\nwith each other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1066000,"text":"So I want to conclude with two things."},{"time":1068129,"text":"I want to conclude with a worry,"},{"time":1070200,"text":"and with a wonderful story."},{"time":1074287,"text":"The worry is about antidepressants."},{"time":1078631,"text":"Over 100 million prescriptions\nof antidepressants"},{"time":1083787,"text":"are written every year\nin the United States."},{"time":1087100,"text":"And these drugs are going generic."},{"time":1089689,"text":"They are seeping around the world."},{"time":1092743,"text":"I know one girl who's been\non these antidepressants,"},{"time":1098000,"text":"SSRIs, serotonin-enhancing\nantidepressants -- since she was 13."},{"time":1102000,"text":"She's 23. She's been on them\never since she was 13."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1105000,"text":"I've got nothing against people\nwho take them short term,"},{"time":1108540,"text":"when they're going\nthrough something horrible."},{"time":1110787,"text":"They want to commit suicide\nor kill somebody else."},{"time":1113166,"text":"I would recommend it."},{"time":1114258,"text":"But more and more people\nin the United States"},{"time":1116741,"text":"are taking them long term."},{"time":1119149,"text":"And indeed, what these drugs do\nis raise levels of serotonin."},{"time":1124974,"text":"And by raising levels of serotonin,\nyou suppress the dopamine circuit."},{"time":1129819,"text":"Everybody knows that."},{"time":1131944,"text":"Dopamine is associated with romantic love."},{"time":1136627,"text":"Not only do they suppress\nthe dopamine circuit,"},{"time":1139801,"text":"but they kill the sex drive."},{"time":1142316,"text":"And when you kill the sex drive,\nyou kill orgasm."},{"time":1146164,"text":"And when you kill orgasm,"},{"time":1147379,"text":"you kill that flood of drugs\nassociated with attachment."},{"time":1151712,"text":"The things are connected in the brain."},{"time":1154000,"text":"And when you tamper with one brain system,"},{"time":1156680,"text":"you're going to tamper with another."},{"time":1159000,"text":"I'm just simply saying that a world\nwithout love is a deadly place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1164738,"text":"So now --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1165764,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1170000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1171727,"text":"I want to end with a story."},{"time":1173839,"text":"And then, just a comment."},{"time":1176741,"text":"I've been studying romantic love\nand sex and attachment for 30 years."},{"time":1183774,"text":"I'm an identical twin;\nI am interested in why we're all alike."},{"time":1187925,"text":"Why you and I are alike,\nwhy the Iraqis and the Japanese"},{"time":1191000,"text":"and the Australian Aborigines\nand the people of the Amazon River"},{"time":1194024,"text":"are all alike."},{"time":1195777,"text":"And about a year ago,"},{"time":1198110,"text":"an Internet dating service,\nMatch.com, came to me"},{"time":1201119,"text":"and asked me if I would design\na new dating site for them."},{"time":1204795,"text":"I said, \"I don't know anything\nabout personality. You know?"},{"time":1207621,"text":"I don't know. Do you think\nyou've got the right person?\""},{"time":1210365,"text":"They said, \"Yes.\""},{"time":1211429,"text":"It got me thinking\nabout why it is that you fall in love"},{"time":1214476,"text":"with one person rather than another."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1216232,"text":"That's my current project;\nit will be my next book."},{"time":1220262,"text":"There's all kinds of reasons"},{"time":1221825,"text":"that you fall in love\nwith one person rather than another."},{"time":1224602,"text":"Timing is important.\nProximity is important."},{"time":1227912,"text":"Mystery is important."},{"time":1229316,"text":"You fall in love with somebody\nwho's somewhat mysterious,"},{"time":1232069,"text":"in part because mystery\nelevates dopamine in the brain,"},{"time":1234771,"text":"probably pushes you\nover that threshold to fall in love."},{"time":1237561,"text":"You fall in love with somebody"},{"time":1239014,"text":"who fits within\nwhat I call your \"love map,\""},{"time":1241133,"text":"an unconscious list of traits"},{"time":1243304,"text":"that you build in childhood\nas you grow up."},{"time":1245642,"text":"And I also think\nthat you gravitate to certain people,"},{"time":1248708,"text":"actually, with somewhat\ncomplementary brain systems."},{"time":1252000,"text":"And that's what I'm now\ncontributing to this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1254311,"text":"But I want to tell you\na story, to illustrate."},{"time":1258000,"text":"I've been carrying on here\nabout the biology of love."},{"time":1261709,"text":"I wanted to show you a little bit\nabout the culture of it, too,"},{"time":1265420,"text":"the magic of it."},{"time":1268000,"text":"It's a story that was told to me"},{"time":1271373,"text":"by somebody who had\nheard it just from one --"},{"time":1273858,"text":"probably a true story."},{"time":1276508,"text":"It was a graduate student --\nI'm at Rutgers and my two colleagues --"},{"time":1280000,"text":"Art Aron is at SUNY Stony Brook."},{"time":1282000,"text":"That's where we put our people\nin the MRI machine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1285000,"text":"And this graduate student was madly\nin love with another graduate student,"},{"time":1289587,"text":"and she was not in love with him."},{"time":1293206,"text":"And they were\nall at a conference in Beijing."},{"time":1296485,"text":"And he knew from our work"},{"time":1299543,"text":"that if you go and do something\nvery novel with somebody,"},{"time":1303975,"text":"you can drive up\nthe dopamine in the brain,"},{"time":1306000,"text":"and perhaps trigger\nthis brain system for romantic love."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1309717,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1311898,"text":"So he decided he'd put science to work."},{"time":1316624,"text":"And he invited this girl to go off\non a rickshaw ride with him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1320809,"text":"And sure enough -- I've never been in one,"},{"time":1322902,"text":"but apparently they go\nall around the buses and the trucks"},{"time":1325664,"text":"and it's crazy and it's noisy\nand it's exciting."},{"time":1328506,"text":"He figured that this\nwould drive up the dopamine,"},{"time":1330816,"text":"and she'd fall in love with him."},{"time":1332372,"text":"So off they go and she's squealing\nand squeezing him"},{"time":1337370,"text":"and laughing and having a wonderful time."},{"time":1339911,"text":"An hour later they get down\noff of the rickshaw,"},{"time":1343474,"text":"and she throws her hands up and she says,"},{"time":1347078,"text":"\"Wasn't that wonderful?\""},{"time":1349414,"text":"And, \"Wasn't that rickshaw\ndriver handsome!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1352852,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1355945,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1362000,"text":"There's magic to love!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1363186,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1364821,"text":"But I will end by saying\nthat millions of years ago,"},{"time":1368465,"text":"we evolved three basic drives:"},{"time":1370821,"text":"the sex drive, romantic love"},{"time":1373364,"text":"and attachment to a long-term partner."},{"time":1375728,"text":"These circuits are deeply\nembedded in the human brain."},{"time":1379203,"text":"They're going to survive\nas long as our species survives"},{"time":1383630,"text":"on what Shakespeare called\n\"this mortal coil.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1386362,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1387392,"text":"Chris Anderson: Helen Fisher!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1388841,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}